    <h5 class="card-title">Red Fort</h5>
    <p class="card-text">The Agra Fort is a historical fort in the city of Agra 
	in India also known as the Red Fort. Built by the Mughal emperor Akbar in 1565 and
	 completed in 1573, it served as the main residence of the rulers
	 of the Mughal Dynasty until 1638, when the capital was shifted from Agra to Delhi.</p>
